t":1,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَرْو","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"}],"frequency_in_corpus":1868,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17160","n17167","n17172"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be well-watered (of a plant)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to drink one's fill [with مِن (min) ‘of a liquid, esp. water’] (of livestock)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17160","headword_ar":"روّى","root":"rwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarowiyapN","text_ar":"تَرْوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4, in two places: ―         -b2-  and 5. [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Alt~arowiyapi","text_ar":"يَوْمُ التَّرْوِيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of providing oneself with water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the eighth day of Dhu-l-Hijjeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the day before that of 'Arafeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) so called because they (the pilgrims, T) used to provide themselves ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yatazaw~aduwna","text_ar":"يَتَزَوَّدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", T, M, or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataraw~awona","text_ar":"يَتَرَوَّوْنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb, and so in a copy of the T, or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarotawuwna","text_ar":"يَرْتَوُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, K) on that day with water (T, S, M, * Msb, K) for the aftertime, (S, Msb, K,) and to rise and go, or when rising to go, to Minè, where is no water, [or, accord. to the Msb, where was little water,] therefore they provided themselves fully with water, or therefore they provided themselves with water from Mekkeh for the alighting and abiding at Minè: (T, accord. to two different copies:) or [it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the day of consideration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thought;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(from another signification of the verb, as will be seen from what follows;) and is so called] because Abraham was considering, or thinking upon, his dream ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa yatafak~aru fiY ruw^oyaAhu","text_ar":"وَ يَتَفَكَّرُ فِى رُوْيَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna yataraw~aY","text_ar":"كَانَ يَتَرَوَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":") [on that day], and on the ninth he knew [that his dream was from God], and on the tenth he desired to act [according to his dream] ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaEomala","text_ar":"اِسْتَعْمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (K. [And in a similar manner it is explained in the Ksh and by Bd in xxxvii. 101. See also 2 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwA^","text_ar":"روا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rw~Y raA^osahu biAld~uhoni","text_ar":"روّى رَاْسَهُ بِالدُّهْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~ariyda biAld~asami","text_ar":"الثَّرِيدَ بِالدَّسَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He moistened"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saturated it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its hair, with oil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the broken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbled, bread with grease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravy"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rw~Ahu Al$~iEora","text_ar":"روّاهُ الشِّعْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mgh, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadiyva","text_ar":"الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n. as above; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAhu","text_ar":"اـِيَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArwAhu","text_ar":"ارواهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to relate by heart the poetry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * Mgh, * K, * TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tradition, narrative,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"story;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him to bear in his memory, knowing by heart, and to transmit, relate, recite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rehearse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the poetry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tradition, narrative,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"story;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he taught him to do so;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he related to him by heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaY lahu","text_ar":"رَوَى لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the poetry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tradition, narrative,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"story,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until he retained it in his memory, for the purpose of relating it by heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as learned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw~iynaA AlHadiyva","text_ar":"رُوِّينَا الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We had the tradition, narrative,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"story, related to us by heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iEora","text_ar":"الشِّعْرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the poetry"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raw~ayotu fiY","text_ar":"رَوَّيْتُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amori","text_ar":"الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, [though Freytag represents the verb as being in the K without teshdeed, and Golius explains the verb nearly in the same manner with and without teshdeed,]) inf. n. as above, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looked into the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case; inspected it; examined it; considered it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thought upon it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deliberately,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leisurely; without haste;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raw~aA^otu","text_ar":"رَوَّاْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (M, TA:) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraw~ayotu","text_ar":"تَرَوَّيْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. signifies the same:] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataraw~aY","text_ar":"يَتَرَوَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the former half of this paragraph, in an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Alt~arowiyapi","text_ar":"يَوْمُ التَّرْوِيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["M","S","Msb","K","T","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n17167","headword_ar":"رِوًى","root":"rwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaA='N","text_ar":"رَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTabN riwFY","text_ar":"رُطَبٌ رِوًى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dates when they ripen"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after they have been cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not upon their palm-trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murowK","text_ar":"مُرْوٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n17172","headword_ar":"رَوِىٌّ","root":"rwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaA='N","text_ar":"رَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"full,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete,"},{"kind":"text","text":"drink. (K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aribotu $urobFA rawiy~FA","text_ar":"شَرِبْتُ شُرْبًا رَوِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I drank a full,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete, drink."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cloud of which the rain-drops are large,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and vehement in their fall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqiY~N","text_ar":"سَقِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowiyapN","text_ar":"اَرْوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  And, accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who gives to drink;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a waterer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqK","text_ar":"سَاقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [in one copy of the T, in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAqiY","text_ar":"السَّاقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"as explanatory of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~awiY~u","text_ar":"الرَّوِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aA^an~iY","text_ar":"التَّاَنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", which I think an evident mistranscription:] ―         -b5-  and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-  and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sound in body and intellect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(All three from the T.)       -A2-  Also The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"funda-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1196},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mental"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rhyme-letter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"letter upon which the ode is founded, and which is indispensable in every verse thereof, in one place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, for instance, the [final]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the verse here following:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA qal~a maAlu Almaro'i qal~a Sadiyquhu\n                      \n                     \n                        wa A^awomato A_ilayohi biAlEuyuwni AlA^aSaAbiEu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the wealth of the man becomes little, his friends become few, and, together with the eyes, the fingers make signs to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Akh, M:) [when two or more letters are indispensable to the rhyme, only one of them is thus termed, according to rules fully explained in the M and in the treatises on versification:] IJ mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawiy~aAtN","text_ar":"رَوِيَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as its pl.; but [ISd says,] I think him to have stated this carelessly, and not to have heard it from the Arabs. (M.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSiydataAni EalaY","text_ar":"قَصِيدَتَانِ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawiY~K waAHidK","text_ar":"رَوِىٍّ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two odes"},{"kind":"text","text":"constructed"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon one rhymeletter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having one fundamental rhyme-letter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K","Akh","M"]}]}}